The definition of child will be the same as for the child tax credit (you’ll find the age and other requirements at that link).
Since we haven’t filed for 2020 yet, the IRS will “advance” your check based on your most recently filed tax return (2018 or 2019 tax return).
Let’s say you’re entitled to a stimulus check for $1,200 and you get your check this year (in 2020).
But what if you didn’t get your stimulus check because you didn’t file in 2018 or 2019 - or some other reason?
Usually, you’d do that on your tax return, but you can also submit a federal form 8822, Change of Address (downloads as a PDF).